cu500_pal | 1 | The first, middle, and last line of each page are written in a beautiful thuluth hand, covering the whole width of the writing space and dividing the page into 2 sections, each containing 3 centered shorter lines written in a clear and delicate naskhi hand.  The vertical strokes of the latter show a tendency to slant downward a little to the right.  The text is fully pointed and voweled.  The first 2 waqf sheets were drawn up by &apos;Abd al-Razzaq and are written in a careful and well-formed hand.  The remaining 3 are in inferior script in contrast with his signature.  The 2nd sheet has a testimony in line with his signature, but in a fine, small hand in a lighter ink.  The 4th sheet also has a testimony.
